cluded. More generally, a finite\neffective cosmological constant compatible with the observational constraints\ncan be obtained as long as the bare masses of the massive matter fields are\nnearly zero, or the conformal invariance of matter is restored at some high\nenergy scale.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 18 Jun 2008 16:22:00 GMT"}],"update_date":"2008-06-19"}
