he 30 GHz channel. The only essential difference found so far between\nmapmaking codes that affects accuracy (in terms of residual RMS) is baseline\nlength. All optimal codes give essentially indistinguishable results. A\ndestriper gives the same result as the optimal codes when the baseline is set\nshort enough. For longer baselines destripers require less computing resources\nbut deliver a noisier map.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 19 Jun 2008 11:32:04 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 17 Nov 2008 16:11:32 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Thu, 9 Apr 2009 06:11:06 GMT"}],"update_date":"2009-06-02"}
